1. create a repository via web page https://github.crafet/Hello-World
2. in the page, copy the repository address, https://github.com/crafet/Hello-World.git
3. in the terminal, kick code as following:
	mkdir Hello-World	## create local reposity dir
	cd Hello-World
	touch README.md
	echo "readme" >> README.md
	git init			## init the repository
	git add .			## add all the file under the git version control
	git commit -m"add commit description"
	git remote add origin https:// github.com/crafet/Hello-World.git
	git diff			## not necessary,but recommend
	git push -u origin master

4. done
5. use "git add xx" whenever xx is modified, it seems different from svn
